    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Simple bronze conical tubes attached to the inside of a guitar’s sound hole that accentuates the instrument’s bass register and directs the sound towards the listener. It is a standard component of many guitars built in the 19th century, but has fallen from use in contemporary guitars.</Note_Text>
